    Class Description
    CommandConstants
    The CommandConstants class announces a group of constants that are needed to access some commands.
    DefaultValueConstants
    The DefaultValueConstants class announces a group of constants which are necessary for initialization defaults class field values by those who receive identical field in the database.
    ExceptionConstants
    The ExceptionConstants class announces a number of constants that are passed in the throw section to determine the concrete exception.
    LogicFlagConstants
    The LogicFlagConstants class announces a group of flags that help to establish the result and the further course of the program.
    MessageConstants
    The MessageConstants class declares a number of constants that are used to transmit the message to the jsp, as well as logging code.
    ParameterConstants
    The ParameterConstants class declares constants group taking the field values of parameters in the database and field names on the JSP to retrieve values from these sources.
    PathConstants
    The PathConstants class announces a group of constants needed to redirect certain JSP pages, as well as to gain access to certain files and directory in the system.
    StateConstants
    The StateConstants class announces four states that can accept the order throughout the life cycle.
    SymbolConstants
    The SymbolConstants class announces a series of characters that are used in the logging code, display messages on JSP and etc.
